        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-intro">
                <h2>How long does the bitcoin advantage last?</h2>
                <p><em>The forward projection &mdash; what the Power Law trend says about the next 10 to 30 years.</em></p>
            </div>

            <p class="prose">The retrospective evidence above answers the question for someone considering a position who would have started at any of the dates the page covers. The forward question for someone deciding right now is: <strong>over the horizon I&rsquo;ll actually hold this, where is the trend headed?</strong></p>

            <p class="prose">The chart below plots the Power Law trend for bitcoin against the long-run historical trend lines for the S&amp;P 500, NASDAQ, and gold, extrapolated forward at each comparator&rsquo;s historical CAGR. The Power Law is a <em>central-tendency expectation</em>, not a forecast &mdash; bitcoin spends roughly half its time above the trend and half below, and deviations within cycles can be very large in either direction. The trend says where bitcoin is most likely to be over the long horizon, not what will happen in any particular year. The same caveat applies to the comparator trends &mdash; the S&amp;P 500 has had stretches of decade-long underperformance and decade-long outperformance against its own long-run CAGR.</p>

